cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT

The paper deals with training deep neural networks, specifically ResNet models, using stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and measuring the mutual information between hidden layers and input image data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the information bottleneck principle, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT) and the use of PixelCNN++ models as inverse representation decoders, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
